description: {"blocks":[{"key":"3be5g","text":"The European polecat (Mustela putorius) is a mammalian predator which breeds across much of Europe east to central Asia. In Great Britain, following years of persecution the European polecat has recently undergone a population increase due to legal protection and its range now overlaps that of feral domestic ferrets (Mustela putorius furo). During this range expansion, European polecats hybridised with feral domestic ferrets producing viable offspring. Here we carry out population-level whole genome sequencing on domestic ferrets, British European polecats, and European polecats from the European mainland and find high degrees of genome introgression in British polecats outside their previous stronghold, even in those individuals phenotyped as ‘pure’ polecats. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":22,"length":16},{"style":"italic","offset":319,"length":21}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"9499e","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"qcrb","text":"To create ADMIXTURE plots for our data, we used the following pipeline:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3e8n4","text":"BCFTOOLS prune for linkage, reformat the into Plink format, run Structure over a sensible range of K, chooseK and plot with Structure","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dam63","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f6bbj","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cfjlh","text":"Take the linkage pruned dataset from 'Phylogenetics, Step 3.2, and handle missing genotypes","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1mksa","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dg6f7","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"9apdg","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"code_insert","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"92ld","text":"source plink-1.90","type":"unstyled"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"36oi1","text":"plink --bfile dom_ep_snps_plink_stucture --geno 0.999 --make-bed --out dom_ep_snps_plink_stucture_pruned","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"92ljg","text":"Then run on k=2-5","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6gjm7","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"lcfl","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"8o3s7","text":"To identify the best value of K, I used the --cv for bootstrap and CV estimates","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"code_insert","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"7nm91","text":"K=$1","type":"unstyled"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"chjsq","text":"source admixture-1.3.0\nadmixture --cv -j6 dom_ep_snps_plink_stucture_pruned.bed $K","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a8m84","text":"grep out the CV errors to find the best (highest) value of K","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3f1k1","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4anbp","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"2as68","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"code_insert","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"dpvpg","text":"grep \"CV\" *.out | awk '{print $3,$4}' | cut -c 2-4,6,7-20 \u003e ADMIXTURE.cv.error","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ebldv","text":"Plot all of the Admixture plots together.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ubm7","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"414hb","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"code_insert","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"1gpo5","text":"Rscript plotADMIXTURE.R -p dom_ep_snps_plink_stucture_pruned -i k5_sample.map -k 5 -l euro,welsh,english,hybrid,domestic\n","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f2hdc","text":"Run RAxML in two stages. The first is the 'check' and 'parse'  options that check the alignment and creates an *raxml.rba binary  alignment file. It also estimates the resources needed to run RAxML efficiently (cores and memory)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"ehvgi","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"co9b7","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"1as9o","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"6eemt","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"code_insert","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"12tu8","text":"ALIGNMENT=$1 #An alignment in fasta format","type":"unstyled"},{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"cmehm","text":"","type":"unstyled"},{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"4h2ot","text":"source RAxML-NG-0.9.0","type":"unstyled"},{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"d4k55","text":"raxml-ng-mpi --check --msa $ALIGNMENT --model GTR+G --prefix T1","type":"unstyled"},{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"f4vpt","text":"raxml-ng-mpi --parse --msa $ALIGNMENT --model GTR+G --prefix T2","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ca3cn","text":"Using the resources advised by the previous step, run final step to produce the phylogeny.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"c15cu","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"25rpt","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"8lmmi","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"code_insert","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"82lss","text":"source RAxML-NG-0.9.0","type":"unstyled"},{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"dv1ju","text":"raxml-ng-mpi --all --msa T2.raxml.rba --outgroup weasel  --prefix raxml_all --threads 1 --seed 2 --bs-metric fbp,tbe","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3kpsn","text":"The first step is to create a 'clust' file. The clust file contains three columns, where the first and second column both indicate the name of the individual and the third  column indicates the taxon name. This can be achieved by using a combination of bcftools and awk.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"dt7m0","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"9ddmf","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"duukc","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"code_insert","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"bpj0d","text":"source bcftools-1.9 bcftools query -l$FILE.vcf.gz | awk'{split($1,pop,\".\"); print $1\"\\t\"$1\"\\t\"pop[2]}'\u003e mustelids.clust\n","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cin2l","text":"Next, we need as input a VCF file that has been pruned for linkage- disequilibrium (LD).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"7t14o","text":"The input for this is the 'all_samples_genotyped_snps.vcf' file produced here:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"b6ijs","text":"https://www.protocols.io/view/gatk-nuclear-variant-discovery-and-consensus-assem-bqzgmx3w?step=2.2","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":98}],"data":[]},{"key":"8lk63","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"aqhpk","text":"We filtered for an LD of 0.8 over windows of 5Kb","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"3sukm","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"57d96","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":1,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"f31j8","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"","data":{"guid":"77503001EEC711EBAA260A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://www.protocols.io/view/gatk-nuclear-variant-discovery-and-consensus-assem-bqzgmx3w?step=2.2"}},"1":{"type":"code_insert","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"eprh","text":"source bcftools-1.9","type":"unstyled"},{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"amvua","text":"bcftools +prune -l 0.8 -w 5000 all_samples_genotyped_snps.vcf -Oz -o all_samples_genotyped_snps_ld_0.8.vcf.gz","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}
